paper_abstract: The Biot model is widely used to model poroelastic media. Several authors have tested its applicability to cancellous bone, but to do so requires a priori estimation of the parameters of the Biot model, which is an uncertain and expensive endeavor. A method of computing acoustic pressure in the low 100 kHz range is developed. (c) 2006 Elsevier Ltd. All rights reserved.
paper_title: Determination of the parameters of cancellous bone using high frequency acoustic measurements
